        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-06T15:48:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I went over this again and made it handle multiple overlapped slots and the case where a single slot gets split, and hax_set_ram is never called with an overlapping range.\n\nSo if I understand correctly, SET_RAM2 is a new ioctl api for HAXM where we can invalidate slots by ids and slot id\u0027s will always be disjoint? What if the user on the QEMU side wants to merge or split regions?",
      "parentUuid": "e160235e_bf31fce6",
      "revId": "a411d8ef278aa9583e096909adeb0c2f66df4e10",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
