      "message": "Both here and line 148 above pass the original region to SET_RAM2, which may still overlap with partial or more than one existing slot that HAXM keeps track of, so HAXM needs to do similar manipulations of slots (splitting, resizing, etc.).\nIn a comment above I outlined another algorithm, which guarantees that we only pass to HAXM either a completely new region (no overlap with existing slots), or a region that perfectly coincides with a single existing slot (which is to be updated or deleted). I hope it can be implement in this patch, so we can avoid doing the slot manipulations twice. (I also wanted to see the use of slot ids, but that can wait.)",
